 Blog Post Structure for hyperbliss.tech:

Location:
- All blog posts must be placed in src/posts/ directory
- Use date-prefixed filenames: YYYY.MM.DD_post-title.md
- Filename becomes the URL slug: /blog/YYYY.MM.DD_post-title

Frontmatter Requirements:
- title: String - Descriptive title (can include emoji)
  Example: "ðŸŽ­ HyperShell: Unifying Windows and Linux"
- date: String - ISO format or YYYY-MM-DD
- author: String - Name of the author (default: "Stefanie Jane")
- excerpt: String - Brief summary (1-3 sentences, 150-200 chars)
- tags: String[] - 4-7 relevant topics as kebab-case

Content Structure:
1. Introduction (1-2 paragraphs)
   - Set the tone and introduce the topic
   - Can use either regular paragraphs or an H2 heading (## ðŸŒŸ Introduction)

2. Main Content Sections (H2 headings)
   - Use emoji prefixes for section headings
   - Organize content in logical sections with H2 headings
   - Use H3 for subsections 
   - Keep paragraphs concise (3-5 sentences)

3. Rich Content Elements:
   - Code blocks with language specifiers (```language)
   - Tables using markdown table syntax (| header | header |)
   - Lists (both ordered and unordered)
   - Blockquotes for emphasis or quotes
   - Horizontal rules (---) to separate major sections

4. Visual Elements:
   - Use emoji to emphasize points
   - Include "Pro Tips" or "Examples" with custom formatting
   - Use bold and italic text for emphasis
   - Use backticks for inline code or technical terms

5. Conclusion (Optional)
   - Summarize key takeaways
   - Can use either regular paragraphs or an H2 heading

Writing Style:
- Conversational but authoritative tone
- Technical accuracy with accessibility to various skill levels
- Use first person when sharing personal experience
- Use second person when providing instructions
- Include questions to engage readers
- Maintain cyberpunk/tech aesthetic in examples and references

Length Guidelines:
- Short-form: 800-1200 words
- Medium-form: 1200-2000 words
- Long-form: 2000-3000 words
- Technical deep-dives can exceed 3000 words with proper sectioning